00:48:11.507 --> 00:48:12.505
JP: Roger?

813
00:48:12.508 --> 00:48:15.509
(SIGHS)
You can forget that dime.

814
00:48:18.507 --> 00:48:21.506
Do you think your parents
are gonna ever come get you?

815
00:48:23.500 --> 00:48:28.502
I don't know. Mom's not alive,
but my dad's gonna come get me.

816
00:48:29.501 --> 00:48:30.507
ROGER: I'm sure of it.

817
00:48:31.505 --> 00:48:34.500
You think my mom's
gonna ever come get me?

818
00:48:35.502 --> 00:48:37.500
Maybe, you know.

819
00:48:38.500 --> 00:48:39.508
It could happen.

820
00:48:40.509 --> 00:48:43.507
Yeah, it could happen.

821
00:48:48.503 --> 00:48:50.508
- JP: Roger?
- What?

822
00:48:51.506 --> 00:48:53.507
I'm happy you see the angels.

823
00:48:57.502 --> 00:48:58.503
Me too.

824
00:49:01.503 --> 00:49:03.500
JP: Good night.

825
00:49:08.501 --> 00:49:10.504
RANCH: It's a beautiful day
here in Anaheim...

826
00:49:10.505 --> 00:49:13.505
as the resurgent Angels
prepare to meet their longtime

827
00:49:13.506 --> 00:49:15.504
nemesis, the Detroit Tigers...

828
00:49:15.505 --> 00:49:18.507
who have won the first five games
of their Western road trip.

829
00:49:19.501 --> 00:49:22.500
