00:55:00.502 --> 00:55:04.500
And we're down in the Angels' clubhouse
for a talk with manager George Knox.

907
00:55:04.500 --> 00:55:07.500
- What inspired you to start Mel?
- A feeling.

908
00:55:07.500 --> 00:55:09.504
An instinct. A kind of faith.

909
00:55:09.505 --> 00:55:12.503
A faith in what? Has Mel shown
this kind of power in practice?

910
00:55:13.500 --> 00:55:16.501
Mel Clark has always shown himself
to be an extraordinary athlete.

911
00:55:16.508 --> 00:55:19.504
The rest is about believing
in something or someone.

912
00:55:19.504 --> 00:55:21.504
And when did you suddenly start
believing in Clark?

913
00:55:21.505 --> 00:55:23.501
He's been sitting on
the bench all season.

914
00:55:24.502 --> 00:55:27.500
- I look for signs.
- It's good to win.

915
00:55:27.501 --> 00:55:29.505
GEORGE: And sometimes they come
from unexpected places.

916
00:55:29.508 --> 00:55:32.506
Look, that's enough out of me for today.
Talk to the star of the game.

917
00:55:32.509 --> 00:55:33.508
Excuse me.

918
00:55:38.500 --> 00:55:39.505
Something's goin' on.

919
00:55:41.501 --> 00:55:43.505
- Mel! You talk to us about the game.
- Yeah!

920
00:55:44.502 --> 00:55:46.506
Well, it-- it feels great
to be a winner again.

921
00:55:46.508 --> 00:55:49.506
- We won! - (CHUCKLES)
- Yeah. Three in a row.

922
00:55:49.507 --> 00:55:53.504
- Oh, I feel good!
- Yeah. Me too.

923
00:55:54.508 --> 00:55:58.502
- Me three.
- Ah, I owe you guys.

924
00:55:59.501 --> 00:56:01.501
GEORGE: Okay. Anything you want.

925
00:56:01.505 --> 00:56:03.506
You name it, you got it.

926
00:56:04.500 --> 00:56:06.500
(JAZZ PLAYING)

927
00:56:06.500 --> 00:56:09.503
- All right, let's play ball!
- BOYS: Yeah!

928
00:56:10.503 --> 00:56:12.501
- I got third!
- Spread out, guys.

929
00:56:12.501 --> 00:56:14.501
(EXCLAIMING)

930
00:56:14.507 --> 00:56:16.501
(BOYS CLAMORING)

931
00:56:16.501 --> 00:56:20.501
Slow and easy.
Keep your elbows up.

932
00:56:21.509 --> 00:56:23.501
Here it comes.

933
00:56:24.508 --> 00:56:27.501
Great hit, JP!

934
00:56:27.507 --> 00:56:29.506
Get it, Roger! Get it! Get it!

935
00:56:30.502 --> 00:56:32.501
Yeah! All right!

936
00:56:32.504 --> 00:56:34.509
-All right, J.P.
-All right! Who's next?

937
00:56:35.500 --> 00:56:38.500
BOYS: Me! Me! Me!
Me! Me! Me!

938
00:56:39.505 --> 00:56:41.503
Let's give the kid
over on the car a shot.

939
00:56:41.504 --> 00:56:42.507
(BOYS GROAN)

940
00:56:45.503 --> 00:56:48.502
- What's your name?
- Marvin Vincent Archer.

941
00:56:48.505 --> 00:56:50.501
You play any ball before, Marvin?

942
00:56:50.503 --> 00:56:52.500
No, I never played any ball.

943
00:56:52.506 --> 00:56:55.500
Well, this is a perfect time to learn.

944
00:56:55.501 --> 00:56:56.500
Come on.

945
00:56:56.506 --> 00:56:57.505
- GEORGE: Watch the ball...
- ROGER: Stay sharp, Zack.

946
00:56:57.506 --> 00:57:00.507
and when I say "now," you swing.

947
00:57:01.502 --> 00:57:04.506
GEORGE: Just do exactly what I say.
Get ready to swing.

948
00:57:05.500 --> 00:57:07.501
- Now! Oh, oh!
- Yeah, Marvin!

949
00:57:07.502 --> 00:57:08.507
Go, Marvin! Run to first base.

950
00:57:08.507 --> 00:57:10.506
- Nice one. Go!
- Nice hit, nice hit.

951
00:57:15.501 --> 00:57:17.504
You stay on base
and do just what I say.

952
00:57:17.505 --> 00:57:18.507
Okay.

953
00:57:19.501 --> 00:57:22.504
We got runners on first and second.

954
00:57:26.504 --> 00:57:28.507
And look who's comin' to bat--

955
00:57:28.507 --> 00:57:29.505
Babe Ruth.

956
00:57:35.502 --> 00:57:36.506
(GROWLS ANGRILY)

957
00:57:40.501 --> 00:57:42.502
- (GRUNTS)
- Whoa!

958
00:57:43.509 --> 00:57:45.502
Go, Marvin! Run home!

959
00:57:45.503 --> 00:57:46.509
- Run home?
- Run home!

960
00:57:47.502 --> 00:57:48.505
Run home. Run home.

961
00:57:49.505 --> 00:57:51.502
MARVIN: Run home. Run home.

962
00:57:52.506 --> 00:57:54.500
GEORGE: Hey, Marvin,
where ya going?

963
00:57:54.501 --> 00:57:55.505
MARVIN: Run home. Run home.

964
00:57:55.508 --> 00:57:57.500
GEORGE: Hey. W-Where's he goin'?

965
00:57:57.509 --> 00:57:59.509
- Eh, what happened?
- You told him to run home.

966
00:58:00.500 --> 00:58:01.501
- I--
- He did.

967
00:58:02.500 --> 00:58:04.503
(GEORGE LAUGHING)

968
00:58:09.507 --> 00:58:10.506
(BASS GRUNTS)

969
00:58:11.507 --> 00:58:13.508
(CHEERING)

970
00:58:15.505 --> 00:58:18.505
(PLAYING "TAKE ME
OUT THE BALL GAME")

971
00:58:25.403 --> 00:58:27.000
(SCREAMING)

972
00:58:27.924 --> 00:58:28.924
(GROANS)

973
00:58:34.500 --> 00:58:35.508
(LAUGHS)

974
00:58:36.504 --> 00:58:38.503
(LAUGHING CONTiNUES)

975
00:58:38.509 --> 00:58:41.508
GEORGE: You call that a call?
You call that a call?

976
00:58:42.501 --> 00:58:44.509
In all my years of baseball,
I have never seen such a--

977
00:58:45.503 --> 00:58:48.500
such an astute evaluation...

978
00:58:48.503 --> 00:58:51.503
of a potentially
difficult decision.

979
00:58:52.501 --> 00:58:53.506
Masterful call.

980
00:58:54.500 --> 00:58:56.503
Oh, have a nice day.

981
00:58:57.500 --> 00:58:58.500
(GRUNTS)

982
00:58:59.506 --> 00:59:01.506
Fair ball!

983
00:59:07.503 --> 00:59:08.503
Yeow!

984
00:59:14.503 --> 00:59:16.205
(MESSMER SCREAMING)

985
00:59:18.506 --> 00:59:19.506
UMPIRE: Safe!

986
00:59:20.501 --> 00:59:23.502
Yeah! Yeah!
Whooooo!

987
00:59:24.505 --> 00:59:26.507
- Yeah!
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah!

988
00:59:32.600 --> 00:59:33.508
Here you go, black man.

989
00:59:33.508 --> 00:59:36.503
- Thanks!
- Thanks, Mel!

990
00:59:36.507 --> 00:59:37.508
- Hey!
- (LAUGHS)

991
00:59:37.509 --> 00:59:38.508
Oh! It's-

992
00:59:45.000 --> 00:59:46.314
(ALL SCREAMING)

993
00:59:46.339 --> 00:59:47.532
RANCH: Unbelievable!

994
00:59:49.500 --> 00:59:51.500
-(CROWD CHEERING LOUDLY)
-(KNOX LAUGHING)

995
00:59:55.502 --> 00:59:56.502
Get out of the way!

996
00:59:58.883 --> 01:00:00.183
(GROANS)

997
01:00:04.508 --> 01:00:06.505
ALL: Yeah!

998
01:00:07.509 --> 01:00:08.508
(KISSES)

999
01:00:18.508 --> 01:00:21.508
- You're outta there!
- Yeah! Hey?

1000
01:00:23.507 --> 01:00:24.505
No?

1001
01:00:48.502 --> 01:00:50.508
(ALL CHEERING LOUDLY)

1002
01:01:01.501 --> 01:01:04.501
RANCH: The Angels have closed out the
season with an incredible hot streak.

1003
01:01:04.504 --> 01:01:08.503
Who would have believed they could go
from last place at the All-Star break...

1004
01:01:08.503 --> 01:01:11.502
to just one win away
from clinching the division title?

1005
01:01:11.505 --> 01:01:13.507
Now it all comes down
to the last two games of the season...

1006
01:01:13.508 --> 01:01:18.502
and, ironically, they are with the
defending champion Chicago White Sox...

1007
01:01:18.504 --> 01:01:20.509
who are one game back
and closing fast...

1008
01:01:20.509 --> 01:01:24.502
in a determined effort
to deny the Angels the championship.

1009
01:01:24.506 --> 01:01:28.508
The first ofthose crucial games
takes place right here...

1010
01:01:30.506 --> 01:01:32.500
this afternoon.

1011
01:01:35.509 --> 01:01:37.508
- What's it say?
- Thanks. Bye.

1012
01:01:37.508 --> 01:01:38.509
ROGER: Van's gonna
pick us up at 12:00.

1013
01:01:39.501 --> 01:01:41.508
- Rog-- Stupid thing. Roger.
- (DIALS PHONE)

1014
01:01:41.509 --> 01:01:43.509
- ROGER: Huh?
- That was your social worker.

1015
01:01:44.502 --> 01:01:45.501
What does she want?

1016
01:01:45.502 --> 01:01:48.500
MAGGIE: Your hearing's
been changed to this afternoon.

1017
01:01:49.503 --> 01:01:51.509
- But I got a game this afternoon.
- I know.

1018
01:01:52.502 --> 01:01:56.501
I've just tried everything to get 'em
to reschedule. It's just not possible.

1019
01:01:56.507 --> 01:01:58.502
Maggie, I'm not going.

1020
01:02:00.504 --> 01:02:01.509
You don't have a choice,
sweetheart.

1021
01:02:02.507 --> 01:02:04.504
Well, what about George?
What about the Ang-

1022
01:02:04.504 --> 01:02:05.508
I'll call Mr Knox.

1023
01:02:06.503 --> 01:02:08.507
I know he thinks you guys
are his lucky charms...

1024
01:02:09.501 --> 01:02:10.507
but this is just something
you have to do.

1025
01:02:12.500 --> 01:02:14.509
JP can go to the game,
and we'll just try real hard...

1026
01:02:15.500 --> 01:02:16.504
to get you there before it's over.

1027
01:02:17.500 --> 01:02:18.502
It's all I can do.

1028
01:02:18.507 --> 01:02:20.502
ROGER: Aw, man!

1029
01:02:21.507 --> 01:02:23.502
And what about the game?

1030
01:02:24.506 --> 01:02:27.501
ANNOUNCER: Attention,
youngsters age 6 to 16...

1031
01:02:27.502 --> 01:02:29.507
be sure to join the
Junior Angel Fan Club.

1032
01:02:30.501 --> 01:02:32.508
For just five dollars,
you'll receive game tickets...

1033
01:02:33.502 --> 01:02:35.504
baseball cards, a free autograph--

1034
01:02:35.505 --> 01:02:38.409
RANCH: The Southern California
sun is shining, the field is ready...

1035
01:02:38.412 --> 01:02:44.405
the hot dogs are warm, and there's
not an empty seat in the house.

1036
01:02:47.505 --> 01:02:48.502
I know. I know.

1037
01:02:48.503 --> 01:02:51.502
Don't even say it. A large Coke,
two dogs, three Cracker Jacks.

1038
01:02:51.502 --> 01:02:53.509
And I was thinking of getting him a car.
And maybe a corporate jet.

1039
01:02:53.509 --> 01:02:55.501
- And maybe a--
- S-Still no Roger.

1040
01:02:55.508 --> 01:02:57.507
He'll be here any second.

1041
01:02:58.503 --> 01:03:00.507
Of all the days to haul
the kid off to court.

1042
01:03:01.500 --> 01:03:02.508
Why didn't Maggie say
he was sick or somethin'?

1043
01:03:03.501 --> 01:03:06.503
That'd be lying.
Maggie would never lie.

1044
01:03:06.503 --> 01:03:08.500
Well, Maggie's not
in a pennant race.

1045
01:03:08.505 --> 01:03:12.502
ANNOUNCER: Number 19,
third baseman Bruce Shea.

1046
01:03:14.509 --> 01:03:17.506
- Hey, you don't see anything, do you?
- Maybe.

1047
01:03:26.501 --> 01:03:27.503
Huh?

1048
01:03:33.500 --> 01:03:34.502
Sorry.

1049
01:03:36.508 --> 01:03:38.503
Well, it's not your fault.

1050
01:03:39.505 --> 01:03:42.501
You never seen angels before.
Why should you now?

1051
01:03:43.507 --> 01:03:45.503
Hey, it could happen.

1052
01:03:51.500 --> 01:03:53.507
(PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

1053
01:04:02.506 --> 01:04:05.505
You understand that once
this hearing has established...

1054
01:04:05.505 --> 01:04:07.505
Roger's permanent
placement status...

1055
01:04:07.506 --> 01:04:11.502
his welfare will forever forward
be determined by this court.

1056
01:04:13.500 --> 01:04:16.506
- I understand.
- And you've consulted a lawyer?

1057
01:04:19.500 --> 01:04:21.509
Look, lady, I get what I'm doin'.
The kid's not mine any more.

1058
01:04:22.502 --> 01:04:23.503
I'm not proud of it.

1059
01:04:24.503 --> 01:04:26.504
It's not something I could
change my mind about either.

1060
01:04:32.501 --> 01:04:33.506
We're ready to see you now, Roger.

1061
01:04:45.506 --> 01:04:46.506
Dad?

1062
01:04:48.508 --> 01:04:50.506
ROGER: Dad, I didn't know
you were gonna be here!

1063
01:04:50.506 --> 01:04:52.507
You know the Angels are
only one game from the pennant?

1064
01:04:52.508 --> 01:04:55.500
Can you believe it?
It's just like you said!

1065
01:04:59.503 --> 01:05:01.509
- Sorry, boy.
- Dad?

1066
01:05:03.503 --> 01:05:06.500
Hey, Dad, wh--
Did you hear what I said?

1067
01:05:07.507 --> 01:05:08.508
Where ya goin'?

1068
01:05:12.506 --> 01:05:13.504
Daddy?

1069
01:05:22.500 --> 01:05:24.501
- Don't cry.
- Come back.

1070
01:05:24.508 --> 01:05:26.508
(CRYING)

1071
01:05:30.500 --> 01:05:32.000
(THUMPING)

1072
01:05:38.502 --> 01:05:40.134
(CRYING) But, we lost!

1073
01:05:40.159 --> 01:05:42.508
(STAMMERS) Don't cry.
It's only a game.

1074
01:05:42.508 --> 01:05:45.509
Come on. You're getting snot all over
the place. It's nobody's fault.

1075
01:05:46.500 --> 01:05:49.504
I tried to see angels.
I really tried.

1076
01:05:49.505 --> 01:05:54.502
I guess without angels helping,
this team doesn't have what it takes.

1077
01:05:54.506 --> 01:05:56.508
Maybe I just don't
have what it takes.

1078
01:05:56.509 --> 01:06:01.501
JP: If we could still win
without the angels. It could happen.

1079
01:06:02.506 --> 01:06:06.504
Maybe. Eh, gimme a minute, kid,
and I'll be out to take you home.

1080
01:06:06.506 --> 01:06:08.509
But, don't cry.

1081
01:06:10.501 --> 01:06:11.502
MAN: No, we're not.

1082
01:06:16.504 --> 01:06:17.509
Hey, put out that cigarette.

1083
01:06:20.504 --> 01:06:21.506
Hey.

1084
01:06:23.501 --> 01:06:28.502
RANCH: I'm Ranch Wilder the
voice of the Angels.

1085
01:06:30.506 --> 01:06:33.505
I know who you are.
I heard you on the radio.

1086
01:06:34.501 --> 01:06:36.504
JP: You sure do
have a big chin.

1087
01:06:37.500 --> 01:06:38.506
Everybody's a critic.

1088
01:06:40.506 --> 01:06:43.500
- Well, what's your name?
- JP.

1089
01:06:43.500 --> 01:06:45.502
RANCH: Well, J.P., that was
a tough loss today, huh?

1090
01:06:45.507 --> 01:06:49.501
Knox took it pretty hard.
He was gettin' kinda crazy out there.

1091
01:06:49.503 --> 01:06:51.501
'Cause Roger couldn't come.

1092
01:06:52.501 --> 01:06:54.504
I get it. So Roger's sort of lucky.
Is that it?

1093
01:06:54.506 --> 01:06:59.505
He sees the angels, the ones
who help out. He prayed for 'em.

1094
01:06:59.509 --> 01:07:04.506
- Real angels?
- Yeah, but I don't see 'em.

1095
01:07:06.501 --> 01:07:08.507
And Knox-- he sees 'em?

1096
01:07:09.506 --> 01:07:10.506
No!

1097
01:07:10.506 --> 01:07:13.501
Roger has to tell him
when they're around.

1098
01:07:14.502 --> 01:07:15.507
Really?

1099
01:07:18.509 --> 01:07:20.508
MAGGIE: You know,
by releasing you legally...

1100
01:07:21.506 --> 01:07:24.503
it does make it possible for somebody
to take you permanently.

1101
01:07:26.500 --> 01:07:27.509
He did that 'cause he wants
the best for you.

1102
01:07:28.505 --> 01:07:32.500
Yeah. Givin' someone away is
a great way to show 'em you care.

1103
01:07:40.509 --> 01:07:44.503
- Hey, Roger!
- Took a little longer than you expected.

1104
01:07:44.509 --> 01:07:49.501
We waited three hours for his hearing.
That's quick for family court.

1105
01:07:49.502 --> 01:07:52.508
- What'd they decide?
- Oh, it's just a formality.

1106
01:07:53.507 --> 01:07:54.509
(CLOSES DOOR)

1107
01:07:55.505 --> 01:07:57.507
He belongs to the state
of California now.

1108
01:08:00.509 --> 01:08:02.500
Scoot over.

1109
01:08:14.508 --> 01:08:16.503
Roger, I'm sorry about today.

1110
01:08:17.501 --> 01:08:20.501
Why? 'Cause you lost
your stupid baseball game?

1111
01:08:21.508 --> 01:08:24.505
No. Because you're hurt.

1112
01:08:25.500 --> 01:08:27.500
(SCOFFS) You don't
know anything about it.

1113
01:08:33.505 --> 01:08:36.509
You know, Roger, when I was growin' up,
I never saw very much of my dad.

1114
01:08:38.502 --> 01:08:40.500
GEORGE: He couldn't
take care of himself...

1115
01:08:41.500 --> 01:08:44.508
so takin' care of me and my brothers
was outta the question.

1116
01:08:49.500 --> 01:08:51.508
I'm not sure the pain
that caused ever goes away.

1117
01:08:53.508 --> 01:08:57.504
But I am sure you can't
go through life...

1118
01:08:57.509 --> 01:09:00.505
thinkin' everyone you meet
will one day let you down.

1119
01:09:02.506 --> 01:09:06.505
Because if you do,
a very bad thing will happen.

1120
01:09:10.506 --> 01:09:12.505
You'll end up like me.

1121
01:09:15.506 --> 01:09:17.500
I'm goin' inside.

1122
01:09:19.502 --> 01:09:21.502
I thought you said you
had to be somewhere.

1123
01:09:23.504 --> 01:09:26.501
I do. Right here.

1124
01:09:28.504 --> 01:09:30.505
- Yuck!
- You both wash your hands?

1125
01:09:30.505 --> 01:09:34.505
- Yep.
- Okay, then, let's dig in.

1126
01:09:36.508 --> 01:09:40.505
GEORGE: Next time I'll try lasagna.
You guys like lasagna?

1127
01:09:41.501 --> 01:09:43.502
BOTH: No. What is it?

1128
01:09:44.502 --> 01:09:47.506
JP: Look. It's God's thumbnail.

1129
01:09:49.505 --> 01:09:51.501
That's just the moon, JP.

1130
01:09:52.505 --> 01:09:54.504
No God up there.

1131
01:09:54.507 --> 01:09:55.509
(BASEBALL THUMPING)

1132
01:10:00.503 --> 01:10:04.504
I can't believe you said that.
The kid who sees angels.

1133
01:10:06.507 --> 01:10:09.503
I don't believe
in angels any more.

1134
01:10:10.501 --> 01:10:12.502
JP: Roger, what are
you talking about?

1135
01:10:12.507 --> 01:10:14.501
That's okay, JP.

1136
01:10:15.504 --> 01:10:17.500
Roger's had a tough day.

1137
01:10:28.508 --> 01:10:30.500
(ROGER SIGHS)

1138
01:10:45.500 --> 01:10:48.502
"The source says there's
a boy known as Roger--

1139
01:10:48.502 --> 01:10:51.509
Even watches games on TV
when the team is out of town...

1140
01:10:52.500 --> 01:10:54.503
and reports to manager Knox
over the phone."

1141
01:10:55.500 --> 01:10:56.505
What's a source?

1142
01:10:57.507 --> 01:11:00.501
- The person who told.
- Oh.

1143
01:11:01.500 --> 01:11:03.506
"And when Mel Clark made his
amazing comeback in August...

1144
01:11:03.507 --> 01:11:06.504
it was Roger's--
it was Roger's idea to start him."

1145
01:11:06.505 --> 01:11:10.501
- That's me.
- Who do you think told?

1146
01:11:11.502 --> 01:11:14.507
I don't know. Maybe David found out.
I don't see how.

1147
01:11:14.508 --> 01:11:18.501
- JP: Are we in trouble?
- Knox is in trouble, that's for sure.

1148
01:11:18.502 --> 01:11:20.507
This is bad, right?

1149
01:11:21.507 --> 01:11:23.503
I'm gonna have to tell Maggie.

1150
01:11:24.507 --> 01:11:26.502
(JP SIGHS)

1151
01:11:27.503 --> 01:11:28.507
WOMAN: Right this
way, Mr Knox.

1152
01:11:31.501 --> 01:11:32.507
You stood me up last night.

1153
01:11:33.509 --> 01:11:37.508
HANK: What in the Sam Hill is
all this about real angels?

1154
01:11:38.504 --> 01:11:40.507
- It's nothing.
- Start talkin'.

1155
01:11:41.502 --> 01:11:43.506
Okay. I-- I got these two kids.

1156
01:11:44.502 --> 01:11:46.500
And I-I think of them as mascots.

1157
01:11:48.501 --> 01:11:51.504
And the angels-- Uh, well--

1158
01:11:52.507 --> 01:11:55.505
It's just something that's
going on between me and them.

1159
01:11:55.505 --> 01:11:58.504
HANK: You're tellin' me there's
real angels in the ball park?

1160
01:11:58.505 --> 01:12:01.504
Sometimes.
But they're not in on all the plays.

1161
01:12:01.505 --> 01:12:02.507
(CHUCKLES)

1162
01:12:02.507 --> 01:12:05.507
- You've lost it, partner.
- Look, if I lied to you...

1163
01:12:06.501 --> 01:12:09.505
then the angels wouldn't like it,
and they might not come back.

1164
01:12:09.507 --> 01:12:14.501
They're very temperamental.

1165
01:12:14.503 --> 01:12:16.506
Mental is the key word here.

1166
01:12:17.501 --> 01:12:21.507
I'm sorry, George, but I'm relieving you
ofyour management responsibilities.

1167
01:12:22.504 --> 01:12:25.507
You can't do that.
We're only one game away.

1168
01:12:27.501 --> 01:12:31.506
I tell you what. I'll give you 24 hours
to get your head on straight.

1169
01:12:32.500 --> 01:12:34.500
Then I'll call a press conference.

1170
01:12:34.505 --> 01:12:37.507
And you can publicly
renounce this hogwash.

1171
01:12:38.504 --> 01:12:43.500
HANK: George, you repeat any of
the baloney I've heard here...

1172
01:12:43.503 --> 01:12:46.509
we're talkin' the end of
your career in baseball.

1173
01:12:47.507 --> 01:12:49.505
HANK: Have I made myself clear?

1174
01:12:50.500 --> 01:12:51.506
Yes.

1175
01:13:26.500 --> 01:13:27.505
MAN: What's goin' on, Knox?

1176
01:13:32.506 --> 01:13:36.501
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen.
We're gonna make this short and sweet.

1177
01:13:36.501 --> 01:13:39.505
My manager, George Knox here,
has something he'd like to say to ya.

1178
01:13:39.508 --> 01:13:43.504
- George.
- I have a statement I'd like to read.

1179
01:13:45.500 --> 01:13:46.504
There have been reports...

1180
01:13:47.504 --> 01:13:50.509
that I've been using angels
to help the team win.

1181
01:13:55.501 --> 01:13:56.505
MAGGIE: Go on. Go in.

1182
01:13:59.508 --> 01:14:02.508
(ALL CLAMORING)

1183
01:14:12.507 --> 01:14:14.502
I was gonna read a statement...

1184
01:14:17.505 --> 01:14:19.506
but instead,
I'm gonna shoot from the hip.

1185
01:14:25.502 --> 01:14:27.504
You know, there are
a lot of times in sports...

1186
01:14:29.503 --> 01:14:34.500
when there's no logical explanation
why things happen.

1187
01:14:36.501 --> 01:14:38.505
GEORGE: Sometimes a
player gets hot and...

1188
01:14:38.509 --> 01:14:41.507
goes beyond their physical ability.

1189
01:14:42.508 --> 01:14:45.503
Is it just adrenaline?
I don't know.

1190
01:14:46.503 --> 01:14:48.505
But I do believe
